President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Nancy Anderson Speight as a Member of the Federal Labor Relations Authority. Speight currently serves as the Deputy Assistant Secretary of Defense for Civilian Personnel Policy, where she is responsible for managing the Department's civilian workforce. She has previously served as the Regional Director for the Atlanta Regional Office of the FLRA, where she oversaw labor-management relations for non-Postal Service Federal employees. Speight has also held various positions within the FLRA's Office of the General Counsel, where she implemented changes in policy and authored operational manuals for processing representation petitions.